## 6. Priority Roadmap

**Phase 1: MVP Core Automations** *(High Impact, Essential Features)*
- Basic Helpdesk & Ticketing System
- AI Chatbot integrated with a static Knowledge Base
- Manual Ticket Resolution

**Phase 2: AI Learning & Lead Generation**
- AI Chatbot Lead Capture flows (fallback to human ticketing)
- AI FAQ & Knowledge Base Auto-update (learning from resolved tickets)

**Phase 3: Scheduling & Advanced Operations**
- AI Appointment Booking Bot
- Automated Reminder System (Email/WhatsApp/SMS integrations)
- Advanced Analytics Dashboard

---

## 7. Functional Requirements

### 7.1 Admin/Agent Requirements
- Access to a unified dashboard to view and respond to tickets.
- Ability to review, edit, and approve AI-generated FAQ drafts.
- Calendar view to manage AI-booked appointments.
- System configuration settings (working hours, chatbot personality, routing rules).

### 7.2 Customer Requirements
- Ability to search the public Knowledge Base easily.
- Interactive chat widget available on the client website.
- Natural language conversational booking experience.

---

## 8. Non-functional Requirements
- **Availability:** Chatbot and Booking systems must have 99.9% uptime.
- **Performance:** Chatbot response time should be under 2 seconds.
- **Security:** Secure storage of customer PII (Personally Identifiable Information) and lead data.
- **Scalability:** Architecture must support multiple business tenants (SaaS model).

---

## 9. Data Requirements

- **Ticket Data:** Ticket ID, Customer ID, Subject, Status (Open, Pending, Resolved), Priority, Assigned Agent, Transcript/Thread.
- **Knowledge Base Data:** Article ID, Title, Content, Category, Tags, AI-Generated Flag, Approval Status, View Count.
- **Lead Data:** Name, Email, Phone, Company, Source, Captured Date.
- **Appointment Data:** Appointment ID, Customer ID, Scheduled Time, Service Type, Status (Confirmed, Cancelled, Completed).

---

## 10. Integrations Required
- **AI Engine:** Google Gemini / OpenAI (for Chatbot NLP and FAQ Generation)
- **Communication:** WhatsApp Business API, Twilio (SMS), SendGrid/SMTP (Email)
- **Calendars:** Google Calendar API, Microsoft Outlook Calendar
- **Frontend/Backend:** React/Vite, Node.js/Express, MongoDB/PostgreSQL

---

## 11. Business Rules
- The Chatbot must strictly rely on the approved Knowledge Base to avoid hallucinations.
- Any unanswerable question must trigger the Lead Capture/Ticket Creation fallback.
- AI-generated FAQs *must* require human approval before being published to the live KB.
- Appointments cannot be double-booked; real-time calendar checks are mandatory.

---

## 12. Success Metrics
- **Efficiency:** 40%+ deflection of support tickets via the AI Chatbot and KB.
- **Time-saving:** 90% reduction in manual FAQ drafting time.
- **Revenue/Growth:** 30% increase in leads captured outside working hours.
- **Operations:** 50% reduction in appointment no-show rates due to automated reminders.

---

## 13. MVP Scope
The initial version will include:
- A functional Helpdesk dashboard for agents.
- A basic AI Chatbot that answers questions from uploaded documents.
- Lead capture form within the chat widget.
- Basic CRUD operations for the Knowledge Base.

## 14. Out of Scope for MVP
- Complex multi-language support.
- AI Appointment Booking (deferred to Phase 3).
- Full omni-channel integration (Instagram/Facebook Messenger) - MVP will focus on Web Chat.
- Advanced sentiment analysis reporting.

---

## 15. Execution Plan
1. **Requirements Gathering & Architecture:** Finalize tech stack and database schema for SmartSupport AI.
2. **Helpdesk & KB Development:** Build the core ticketing system and manual KB.
3. **AI Integration:** Connect Gemini/LLM to power the Chatbot and the FAQ Auto-update engine.
4. **Testing & QA:** Rigorously test the bot against edge cases and ensure accurate ticket routing.
5. **Phase 1 Launch:** Deploy MVP to early adopters.
6. **Iterate & Expand:** Begin development of the AI Appointment Booking module based on user feedback.

---

## 16. Suggested Pricing Model
- **Basic Tier:** Helpdesk + Manual KB + Basic Chatbot (Fixed monthly fee).
- **Pro Tier:** Adds AI FAQ Auto-update + Lead Capture flows + Analytics.
- **Premium Tier:** Adds AI Appointment Booking + WhatsApp integration + Dedicated support.

---

## 17. Risks & Mitigation
| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| AI Hallucinations | Incorrect info given to users | Restrict LLM context strictly to the internal Knowledge Base; fallback to human on low confidence. |
| Calendar Sync Errors | Double bookings | Use robust locking mechanisms and real-time API checks for calendar sync. |
| Low User Adoption | Product fails | Ensure the Chatbot UI is frictionless and provides clear options to speak to a human. |
| Data Privacy Breaches | Legal/Reputation damage | Implement proper encryption, authentication (JWT), and follow GDPR/data protection guidelines. |

---

## 18. Dependencies
- Availability of LLM API (Gemini/OpenAI) with sufficient rate limits.
- Stable hosting infrastructure (AWS/Vercel/Render).
- Third-party API approvals (e.g., WhatsApp Business API approval process).

---

## 19. Recommended MVP Workflow Architecture
`Customer Web Chat` 
↓
`AI Chatbot Engine (Checks KB)` 
↓ (If answer found) → `Immediate Response`
↓ (If no answer)
`Lead Capture Flow` → `Creates Ticket in Helpdesk`
↓
`Human Agent Resolves Ticket`
↓
`AI Analyzes Resolution` → `Drafts New FAQ` → `Admin Approves` → `Updates KB`

---

## 20. Final Recommendation
Focus initially on perfecting the **AI Chatbot to Helpdesk handoff** and the **FAQ Auto-update loop**. These two features alone provide massive, immediate value by saving time for both the customer and the support agent. Once this core loop is trusted by your users, rolling out the AI Appointment Booking will be a natural and highly anticipated upsell.
